 BY LINUS CHIBUIKE THE Department of State Services, on Friday, has debunked reports that its operatives attempted to arrest Yoruba activist, Sunday Adeyemo, popularly called Sunday Igboho, earlier in the day, in Ibadan, Oyo State. Public Relations Officer, National Headquarters, Abuja, Peter Afunanya, described the report as fake news, and urged the public to disregard it. “The Department of State Services wishes to refute the news that it attempted to arrest one Sunday Igboho, today, at Ibadan, Oyo State,” he said in the short statement. “The said news is misinforming and should be taken as fake and therefore be disregarded,” Afunanya added. 